<item>
            <title>[LU-8091] server_lsi2mti() should return error when fail to get nid</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8091</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;server_lsi2mti() doesn&apos;t return error even if no proper nid is initialized in mti_nids, that would leads to target registered successfully with an illegal empty nid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think server_lsi2mti() should return error if mti_nid_count == 0 after the following loop:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (LNetGetId(i++, &amp;amp;id) != -ENOENT) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (LNET_NETTYP(LNET_NIDNET(id.nid)) == LOLND)
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;

                /* server use --servicenode param, only allow specified
                 * nids be registered */
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((lsi-&amp;gt;lsi_lmd-&amp;gt;lmd_flags &amp;amp; LMD_FLG_NO_PRIMNODE) != 0 &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
                    class_match_nid(lsi-&amp;gt;lsi_lmd-&amp;gt;lmd_params,
                                    PARAM_FAILNODE, id.nid) &amp;lt; 1)
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;

                &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* match specified network */&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!class_match_net(lsi-&amp;gt;lsi_lmd-&amp;gt;lmd_params,
                                     PARAM_NETWORK, LNET_NIDNET(id.nid)))
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;

                mti-&amp;gt;mti_nids[mti-&amp;gt;mti_nid_count] = id.nid;
                mti-&amp;gt;mti_nid_count++;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (mti-&amp;gt;mti_nid_count &amp;gt;= MTI_NIDS_MAX) {
                        CWARN(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Only using first %d nids &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; %s\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
                              mti-&amp;gt;mti_nid_count, mti-&amp;gt;mti_svname);
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;;
                }
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
